<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-06-25T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-06-25T16:00:00-05:00" n="152" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d152">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/5533a</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-06-25T16:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">June 25, 1917, 4 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>5043. Please tell Mr. <persName corresp="#p_BAJ1">Balfour</persName>
                                that Mr. <persName corresp="#p_MH1">Morgenthau</persName> sailed
                                June 21 on steamship <hi rend="italic">Buenos Aires</hi> and should
                                arrive in Cádiz about July 1. Also say that I will be very grateful
                                if he can arrange to have Mr. <persName>Chaim Weizmann</persName>
                                meet Mr. <persName corresp="#p_MH1">Morgenthau</persName> at
                                Gibraltar. I hope you will leave nothing undone to secure Mr.
                                    <persName corresp="#p_BAJ1">Balfour</persName>’s consent, as it
                                is considered most important that Mr. <persName corresp="#p_MH1">Morgenthau</persName> see Mr.
                                <persName>Weizmann</persName>.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>